I"u<p>A long-time consumer of writing on productivity, I’ve noticed it’s easy for me to fall in a trap of analysis paralysis, in which it becomes increasingly difficult to make a decision about what tools and methods to use. This page exists so that I can remind myself of what works, and what doesn.</p>

<h3 id="what-to-do">What to do</h3>
<p>To end a workday feeling fulfilled about what I’ve achieved, it’s best for me to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Pick a particular set of tasks and focus only on them (as opposed to working with a long list of items belonging to a particular “context”, as David Allen would say)</li>
</ul>
